8 Section 2. Section 87-2-705, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "87-2-705. Drawing for special elk permits. (1) In the event the number of valid applications for
10 special elk permits for a hunting district exceeds the quota set by the department for the district, these permits
11 shall be awarded by a drawing. The department shall provide for those persons making valid application for
12 special elk permits a method of selecting first, second, and third choice hunting districts for any drawing held
13 pursuant to this section.
14 (2) Subject to the limitation of subsection (4), a person who owns or is contracting to purchase 640
15 acres or more of contiguous land, at least some of which is used by elk AS DOCUMENTED BY THE DEPARTMENT, in
16 a hunting district where elk permits are awarded under this section shall be issued, upon application, a permit to
17 hunt elk in the hunting district under the terms and conditions of the permit.
18 (3) An applicant who receives a permit under subsection (2) may designate that the permit be
19 issued to an immediate family member or a person employed by the landowner AN EMPLOYEE OF THE
20 LANDOWNER AS DEFINED IN 87-1-266. WHO WORKS FULL TIME AND YEAR-ROUND AS PART OF THE ACTIVE FARM OR
21 RANCH OPERATION. A corporation owning qualifying land under subsection (2) may designate one of its
22 shareholders to receive the permit.
23 (4) Fifteen percent of the special elk permits available each year under this section in a hunting
24 district must be available to landowners under subsection (2).
25 (5) The department may promulgate the rules necessary to implement this section."
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
